item.description:
Come join us for our 3rd annual Yule Celebration to be held in Warren Mass!

As usual we will start the celebration with the Battle of the Oak and Holly King
as we go from the Dark half of the year into the Light half of the year.

There will be an informative Yule discussion on where, and how our Christmas customs originated from earlier pagan ones, what the Sabbat is all about, and ways to celebrate Yule in style!

We will have a pot luck feast, and following that a "pagan" Yankee swap, along with the carving of our wishes on the traditional yule log that will be burned on Yule.

Pot luck sign up will be put up on the list before the meet up-
And anyone wishing to participate in the Pagan Yankee Swap is asked to bring a WRAPPED pagan
type gift (if you would like it, others will too!) Cost range $15-$25

This is a meet-up is always proves to be tons of fun, and a good way to bring in the light
to celebrate the Winter Solstice

Snow date will be Sunday, December 12, 2010.
item.name: 3rd Annual Yule Party
